ProtoDefines:
. "A subset $S$ of the real line is \term{ of Lebesgue measure 
   zero } if for every $\epsilon>0$ there is a finite or 
   infinite sequence of open intervals $I_1$, $I_2$, \dots\ 
   such that \begin{equation} S\subset\bigcup_j I_j 
   \end{equation} and \begin{equation} \sum_{j=1}^n 
   L(I_j)<\epsilon,\quad n\ge1. \end{equation}"
